import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.scatter(data['income'], data['health'])
    plt.xlabel('Income')
    plt.ylabel('Health')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income and health?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    population_by_region = data.groupby('region')['population'].sum()
    population_by_region.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of population across different regions?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    box_plot = data.boxplot(column='health', by='region', grid=False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        box_plot.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("What is the distribution of health across different regions?")
    plt.suptitle("")
    plt.xlabel("Region")
    plt.ylabel("Health")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
